Comments: Woodhouse's Scrub-Jay, Mid Hills Campground, Mojave National Preserve, San Bernardino County, California, 16 Mar 2017, Tom M. Edell

Observation Details: This bird mostly resembled a Woodhouse's, with the main issue being the somewhat bright blue body and the rather bright vent. Coloration (duller blue, less of a breast band, shorter eye line), bill shape, and response to Woodhouse's calls indicate it can't be a pure California, especially in comparison to the other two there, but it quite possibly might be a hybrid.
First time observed along Westerly Creek.  In area with relatively mature vegetation between 24th Pl and 25th Drive.  Very vocal.
